Class GenericPaginator<T extends Thing,U extends java.lang.Enum<U>>

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AllSubredditsPaginator, MySubredditsPaginator, UserContributionPaginator

    public abstract class GenericPaginator<T extends Thing,U extends java.lang.Enum<U>>
extends Paginator<T>
    This class provides a template for Paginators that use only a "where" attribute, such as /user/username/{where}. The way this class assembles the base URI (getBaseUri()) works somewhat differently than other paginators. The formula for creating this URI is as follows: {prefix}{where.name().toLowerCase()}{postfix}. So if getUriPrefix() resulted in "/user/username", the enum value's name was "SUBMITTED", and getUriPostfix() resulted in ".json", then the base URI would be "/user/username/submitted.json".
